  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the differences between Skylake and haswell?",
  "response": "Skylake and Haswell are both microarchitectures developed by Intel for its processors. Here are some key differences between the two:\n\n1. **Generation:**\n   - **Haswell**: It belongs to the 4th generation of Intel Core processors.\n   - **Skylake**: It is part of the 6th generation of Intel Core processors.\n\n2. **Manufacturing Process:**\n   - **Haswell**: Utilizes a 22nm manufacturing process.\n   - **Skylake**: Uses a more advanced 14nm manufacturing process, allowing for better power efficiency and performance.\n\n3. **Performance Improvements:**\n   - **Skylake** generally offers improved performance over Haswell, including higher CPU instructions-per-clock, better integrated graphics, and improved power efficiency.\n\n4. **Graphics:**\n   - **Haswell**: Features Intel HD Graphics 4600.\n   - **Skylake**: Upgrades to Intel HD Graphics 530/520, and also includes support for Intel Iris Graphics, providing better overall graphical performance.\n\n5. **Memory Support:**\n   - **Haswell**: Supports DDR3 memory.\n   - **Skylake**: Supports both DDR3 (L) and DDR4 memory, allowing for faster memory speeds and greater energy efficiency.\n\n6. **Power Efficiency:**\n   - **Skylake** benefits from enhanced power management technologies, resulting in lower power consumption and better battery life for mobile devices compared to Haswell.\n\n7. **Connectivity and IO:**\n   - **Skylake**: Introduces support for modern connectivity standards like Thunderbolt 3 and USB 3.1, offering faster data transfer rates and improved peripheral connectivity.\n\n8. **Instruction Set Enhancements:**\n   - **Skylake** contains newer instruction sets and optimizations, including AVX-512 for more efficient processing of complex computational tasks.\n\n9. **Platform Improvements:**\n   - **Skylake** includes enhancements such as support for Intel Optane memory, increased PCIe lanes, and improved overall system responsiveness.\n\n10. **Overall Architecture:**\n    - While both architectures share some fundamental design principles, Skylake incorporates various tweaks and enhancements that deliver better performance, efficiency, and capabilities compared to Haswell.\n\nThese differences indicate that Skylake generally represents technological advancement over Haswell, with improvements in efficiency, performance, graphics, and support for newer memory and connectivity standards.",
